# Simple Sign — Project Conventions

## Product Identity

- **Product name**: Simple Sign
- **Namespace**: `aph`
- **Package type**: Managed 2GP (AppExchange)
- **DevHub**: `devhub` (jerome@apphero.tech)
- **Scratch org alias**: `SigDev`

## Naming Convention

| Element | Pattern | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| LWC components | `simpleSign<Feature>` | `simpleSignCapture`, `simpleSignViewer` |
| Apex classes | `SimpleSign<Role>` | `SimpleSignController` |
| Apex tests | `SimpleSign<Role>Test` | `SimpleSignControllerTest` |
| Permission Sets | `SimpleSign<Level>` | `SimpleSignAdmin`, `SimpleSignUser` |
| Custom Labels | `SimpleSign_<Name>` | `SimpleSign_SaveSuccess` |
| Label category | `SimpleSign` | — |

## Naming: Product vs. Business Term

- **"Simple Sign"** = product name, brand, marketing (components, permsets, labels, package)
- **"Signature"** = business term, what the user actually does (object, fields, records, list views)

Do NOT put the product name on data-level elements. A signature is a signature.

## Custom Object

`Signature__c` — label "Signature", pluralLabel "Signatures". API name AND labels stay as-is. The object describes the data, not the brand.

## Custom Tabs

| Tab | Type | Label shown |
|-----|------|-------------|
| `Signature__c` | Object tab | "Signatures" (from object pluralLabel) |
| `Simple_Sign_Setup` | LWC tab | "Simple Sign Setup" |

## 2GP Rules

- All custom labels must have `<protected>true</protected>`
- No inline styles in LWC HTML templates — use CSS files
- No XML comments in metadata files (Salesforce strips them on retrieve)
- All components and classes must use API version `66.0`
- Apex controllers must use `with sharing` and enforce CRUD/FLS

## Scratch Org

- Always use `config/project-scratch-def.json` with `"language": "en_US"` (DevHub is on a German instance)
- Default scratch org alias: `SigDev`
- Always set `--set-default` when creating scratch orgs for this project
